trans-unit.source: Provides base definitions for classes that consume XAML input and produce XAML node streams.
trans-unit.target: Gir base definisjoner for klasser som forbruker XAML inndataene, samt lage XAML noden dataflyter.

trans-unit.source: XamlReader is an abstract class and does not provide implementations or definitions that have a working result for all members.
trans-unit.target: Leverer ikke implementeringer eller definisjoner som har fører fungerer for alle medlemmer XamlReader er en abstrakt klasse.

trans-unit.source: Members that do have an implementation in XamlReader are noted in the remarks for that member.
trans-unit.target: Medlemmer som har en implementering i XamlReader er oppført i kommentarene for medlemmet.

trans-unit.source: Specifically, XamlReader has several abstract members that must be implemented, and several virtual members.
trans-unit.target: Nærmere bestemt har XamlReader flere abstrakt medlemmer som må implementeres og flere virtuelle medlemmer.

trans-unit.source: Of the virtual members, <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> and <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A> each provide a default implementation that is appropriate for most cases.
trans-unit.target: Av de virtuelle medlemmene <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>og <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A>hver angi en standard implementering som passer for de fleste tilfeller.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>

trans-unit.source: However, the <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> and <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A> default implementations rely on other expected behavior of the implementing XAML reader; in particular, they rely on the <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> override.
trans-unit.target: Imidlertid den <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>og <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A>standard implementeringer avhenger av andre forventet virkemåte for implementering XAML leseren; spesielt de avhenger av den <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>overstyre.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>

trans-unit.source: <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Dispose%2A> is also a virtual member that has a working default implementation.
trans-unit.target: <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Dispose%2A>er også medlem virtuelle som har en standard implementering fungerer.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Dispose%2A>

trans-unit.source: The following two classes are the most relevant and practical derived classes in .NET Framework XAML Services and the System.Xaml assembly: - <xref:System.Xaml.XamlObjectReader>, which reads an object graph, such as the active object graph of an application at run time.
trans-unit.target: Følgende to klasser er mest relevante og praktiske avledede klasser i .NET Framework XAML Services og System.Xaml samlingen:- <xref:System.Xaml.XamlObjectReader>, som leser en objekt-diagrammet, for eksempel aktive objektet diagrammet med en applikasjon under kjøring.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlObjectReader>

trans-unit.source: - <xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader>, which reads XAML in the form of a XML text file by using a general <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> that loads the file as an intermediary helper class.
trans-unit.target: - <xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader>, som leser XAML i form av en XML-tekstfil ved hjelp av en generell <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>som laster inn filen som en mellomliggende helper klasse.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader>

trans-unit.source: Other XAML readers from other frameworks include <xref:System.Windows.Baml2006.Baml2006Reader> and <xref:System.Activities.Debugger.XamlDebuggerXmlReader>.
trans-unit.target: Andre XAML lesere fra andre rammeverk inkluderer <xref:System.Windows.Baml2006.Baml2006Reader>og <xref:System.Activities.Debugger.XamlDebuggerXmlReader>.</xref:System.Activities.Debugger.XamlDebuggerXmlReader> </xref:System.Windows.Baml2006.Baml2006Reader>

trans-unit.source: XamlReader differs from [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xmldom](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xmldom-md.md)] and <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader> design principles because XamlReader does not have a `Create` method to return underlying default XAML reader implementations.
trans-unit.target: XamlReader er forskjellig fra [!INCLUDE[TLA#tla_xmldom](~/add/includes/tlasharptla-xmldom-md.md)] og <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>utforme prinsippene fordi XamlReader ikke har en `Create` metode til å returnere underliggende standard XAML leseren implementeringer.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader>

trans-unit.source: You must instead instantiate specific derived XAML reader classes by calling their constructors or other class-specific helper APIs.
trans-unit.target: I stedet må du starte bestemte avledede XAML leseren klasser ved å kalle sin konstruktør eller andre klasse-spesifikke helper APIer.

trans-unit.source: Subtree Readers For the most part, you call XamlReader API in the context of specific XAML reader classes that derive from XamlReader.
trans-unit.target: Du kaller XamlReader API i konteksten for en bestemt XAML leseren klasser som er avledet fra XamlReader subtree lesere For mest del.

trans-unit.source: However, in one particular case, you access XamlReader API on a practical XAML reader instance that is not public and not derived from <xref:System.Xaml.XamlObjectReader> or <xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader>.
trans-unit.target: Imidlertid i én tilfellet du får tilgang til XamlReader API på en praktisk XAML leseren-forekomst som ikke er offentlig og ikke avledet fra <xref:System.Xaml.XamlObjectReader>eller <xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlObjectReader>

trans-unit.source: This case is when you call <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>, which returns a XamlReader instance.
trans-unit.target: Dette tilfellet er når du kaller <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>, som returnerer en forekomst av XamlReader.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>

trans-unit.source: In the default implementation, the XamlReader that is returned by this API is an internal class.
trans-unit.target: I standard implementering er XamlReader som returneres av denne APIen en intern klasse.

trans-unit.source: The XamlReader obtained for subtree reading has valid actions for APIs such as <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> and <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>, and those actions are based on the parent reader class.
trans-unit.target: XamlReader hentet for undertre lesing er gyldige handlinger for API-er for eksempel <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>og <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>, og disse handlingene som er basert på klassen. overordnet leseren</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: This design enables the internal class to track the frame level where the subtree was entered.
trans-unit.target: Denne utformingen aktiverer intern klassen for å spore rammen nivået der undertreet ble angitt.

trans-unit.source: The acting subtree XamlReader makes sure that if the current node position is moved beyond the bounds of the subtree, the specific subtree reader reports end-of-file or `null` at the current node.
trans-unit.target: Undertreet fungerer XamlReader sikrer at hvis den gjeldende noden posisjonen flyttes utenfor grensene for undertreet, rapporterer bestemte undertre leseren slutten av filen eller `null` i den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: Notes about subtree reader usage are included on certain XamlReader APIs.
trans-unit.target: Merknader om undertre leseren Bruk er inkludert på bestemte XamlReader APIs.

trans-unit.target: Initialiserer den <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.target: Lukker XAML noden dataflyten.

trans-unit.target: Du må kalle basisklassen å hente <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.IsDisposed%2A>= `true`.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.IsDisposed%2A>

trans-unit.source: When implemented in a derived class, gets a value that reports whether the reader position is at end-of-file.
trans-unit.target: Henter en verdi som rapporterer om posisjonen leseren er på slutten av filen når implementert i en avledet klasse.

trans-unit.source: Subtree readers can call IsEof, with behavior that correctly reflects the bounds of the entered subtree.
trans-unit.target: Undertreet lesere kan kalle IsEof, med virkemåte som gjenspeiler riktig grensene for det angitte undertreet.

trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon, kan du se "Undertre lesere"-delen i <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, eller se <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis posisjonen er under den begrepsmodellen slutten av filen på XAML noden strømmen; Ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.target: Når implementert i en avledet klasse, henter gjeldende medlem posisjonen leseren hvis posisjonen leseren er på en <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlNodeType"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Subtree readers can call Member, with behavior restrictions.
trans-unit.target: Undertreet lesere kan ringe medlem med virkemåte begrensninger.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see the "Subtree Readers" section in <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, or see <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon, kan du se "Undertre lesere"-delen i <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, eller se <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: The current member; or <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>, if the reader position is not on a member.
trans-unit.target: Gjeldende medlem; eller <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>, hvis posisjonen leseren ikke er i et medlem.

trans-unit.source: When implemented in a derived class, gets the XAML namespace information from the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når implementert i en avledet klasse, henter XAML navneområdet informasjonen fra den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: The intended design of this API is to return a non-null result only if the <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A> of the current node is <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>.
trans-unit.target: Tiltenkte utformingen av denne APIen er å returnere et resultat av ikke-null hvis <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>den gjeldende noden er <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>

trans-unit.source: The property does not report the XAML namespace that applies to objects or members in a general scoping sense, as interpreted under a XAML schema context.
trans-unit.target: Egenskapen rapporterer ikke navneområdet XAML som gjelder for objekter eller medlemmer i en generell områdemaskinen meningsløst som tolkes under en XAML skjemaet kontekst.

trans-unit.source: Your application must provide a means to cache information for the acting XAML namespace as it traverses XAML nodes, if you need that information in a manner other than how the XAML schema context reports it to a writer.
trans-unit.target: Programmet må angi en metode til hurtigbufferinformasjon for fungerer XAML navneområdet som den passerer XAML noder Hvis du trenger denne informasjonen på en måte enn hvordan XAML skjemaet konteksten rapporterer den til en skriver.

trans-unit.source: See<xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader.Namespace%2A> for notes on the reference implementation.
trans-unit.target: Se<xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader.Namespace%2A> for merknader referanse implementeringen.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlXmlReader.Namespace%2A>

trans-unit.source: The XAML namespace information, if it is available; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: XAML navneområdet informasjonen, hvis den er tilgjengelig. Ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.target: Når implementert i en avledet klasse, henter typen for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: Subtree readers can call NodeType, with behavior restrictions.
trans-unit.target: Undertreet lesere kan ringe NodeType, med virkemåte begrensninger.

trans-unit.target: Verdien av <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlNodeType"> </xref> opplisting.

trans-unit.source: When implemented in a derived class, provides the next XAML node from the source, if a node is available.
trans-unit.target: Når implementert i en avledet klasse, inneholder den neste XAML noden fra kilde, hvis en node er tilgjengelig.

trans-unit.source: Subtree readers can call Read, with behavior restrictions.
trans-unit.target: Undertreet lesere kan ringe Les, med virkemåte begrensninger.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see the "Subtree Readers" section in <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, or see <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon, kan du se "Undertre lesere"-delen i <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, eller se <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref> if a node is available; otherwise, <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""></xref>.
trans-unit.target: <xref uid="langword_csharp_true" name="true" href=""></xref>Hvis en node er tilgjengelig. Ellers <xref uid="langword_csharp_false" name="false" href=""> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Returns a <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"></xref> that is based on the current <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"></xref>, where the returned <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"></xref> is used to iterate through a subtree of the XAML node structure.
trans-unit.target: Returnerer en <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"> </xref> som er basert på gjeldende <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"> </xref>, der den resulterende <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"> </xref> brukes til å gå gjennom et undertre for XAML noden strukturen.

trans-unit.source: This method has a default implementation and returns a valid <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>.
trans-unit.target: Denne metoden har en standard implementering og returnerer et gyldig <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: The returned <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> is an internal class that restricts certain <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> actions.
trans-unit.target: Det returnerte <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>er en intern klasse som begrenser visse <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>Handlinger.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: The restrictions are consistent with the purpose of reading only a dimensioned subtree of a larger source for a XAML node set, and of returning end-of-file or `null` at the current node when the subtree is exited.
trans-unit.target: Begrensninger er konsekvente å lese bare et dimensioned undertre av en større kilde for et XAML nodesett, og returnerer slutten av filen eller `null` i den gjeldende noden når undertreet er avsluttet.

trans-unit.source: Generally, you should check the current node from the initial <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> to determine whether you need a subtree reader.
trans-unit.target: Vanligvis, må du kontrollere den gjeldende noden fra første <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>å finne ut om du trenger et undertre-leseren.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: How you check this may be implementation-specific; however, avoid creating multiple subtree readers for every subtree.
trans-unit.target: Hvordan du kontrollere at dette kan være implementering, dvs. Unngå å imidlertid opprette flere undertre lesere for hver undertre.

trans-unit.source: In addition, avoid invoking a subtree reader for certain node cases (for example, for <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>) that cannot contain a subtree of nodes.
trans-unit.target: Unngå i tillegg aktivering undertre leser for enkelte tilfeller node (for eksempel for <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>) som ikke kan inneholde et undertre med noder.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>

trans-unit.source: After you obtain a subtree reader, you must call <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> on it to obtain a current node (or call <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A> to obtain a next node).
trans-unit.target: Når du har et undertre leseren, må du kaller <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>for å hente gjeldende node (eller ring <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A>ikke hente en neste node).</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Skip%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: You do not automatically obtain an initial node position from the subtree reader when you create it.
trans-unit.target: Du henter ikke automatisk en opprinnelig node-posisjonen fra undertre leseren når du oppretter den.

trans-unit.source: The reader you obtain by calling ReadSubtree from this default implementation is an internal class.
trans-unit.target: Leseren du få ved å kalle ReadSubtree fra denne standard implementering er en intern klasse.

trans-unit.source: The internal class bases its behavior on the <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> implementation that is being used when ReadSubtree is called.
trans-unit.target: Intern klassen baseres virkemåten på den <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>implementering som brukes når ReadSubtree kalles.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: The purpose of the internal class is to wrap the <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> and general traversal behavior.
trans-unit.target: Formålet med intern klassen er å omslutte den <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>og generell traversering virkemåte.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: The traversal stays within the intended subtree by keeping track of <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>/<xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> pairs or <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>/<xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> pairs.
trans-unit.target: Traversering blir i undertreet ment å holde oversikt over <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>/<xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> par eller <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>/<xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> par.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>

trans-unit.source: It also correctly returns `false` for <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> and `true` for <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.IsEof%2A> when the reader is at the end of the subtree, as defined by its entry point.
trans-unit.target: Den returnerer også riktig `false` for <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>og `true` for <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.IsEof%2A>når leseren er på slutten av undertreet som er angitt av sin inngangspunktet.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.IsEof%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: In general, you assume that any <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> API you call from a subtree reader has the same implementation as the overall <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> except for the traversal bounding behavior.
trans-unit.target: Generelt du anta at alle <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>API du kalle fra undertre leseren har samme implementering som samlede <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>unntatt traversering markeringsramme virkemåte.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: However, ReadSubtree is virtual.
trans-unit.target: ReadSubtree er imidlertid virtuelle.

trans-unit.source: Therefore, a specific <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> implementation can provide behavior that differs from the <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> internal wrapper behavior; and a <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> implementation can even disable subtree reader functionality by returning <xref:System.NotImplementedException> or other exceptions.
trans-unit.target: Derfor en bestemt <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>implementering kan gi virkemåte som er forskjellig fra det <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>intern wrapper virkemåte; og en <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>implementering kan også deaktivere undertre leseren funksjonalitet ved å returnere <xref:System.NotImplementedException>eller andre unntak.</xref:System.NotImplementedException> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: A new XAML reader instance for the subtree.
trans-unit.target: En ny XAML leseren-forekomst for undertreet.

trans-unit.source: When implemented in a derived class, gets an object that provides XAML schema context information for the information set.
trans-unit.target: Når implementert i en avledet klasse, får du et objekt som gir XAML skjemainformasjon konteksten for settet med opplysninger.

trans-unit.source: An object that provides XAML schema context information for the information set.
trans-unit.target: Angi et objekt som gir XAML skjemainformasjon konteksten for informasjonen.

trans-unit.source: Skips the current node and advances the reader position to the next node.
trans-unit.target: Hopper over gjeldende node og flytter leseren posisjonen til den neste noden.

trans-unit.source: Once skipped, <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> is called by the default Skip implementation.
trans-unit.target: Når hoppet over, <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>kalles av standard Skip implementering.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: You typically do not call Skip and <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> in sequence.
trans-unit.target: Du vanligvis ikke kaller Skip og <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>i rekkefølge.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>

trans-unit.source: In the default Skip implementation, different actions are taken depending on which <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A> the reader position is currently on.
trans-unit.target: Annen handlinger utføres i standard Skip implementering, avhengig av hvilken <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>leseren posisjonen er aktivert.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>

trans-unit.source: If the reader position is currently on a <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> or <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>, that member or object is skipped.
trans-unit.target: Hvis posisjonen leseren er for øyeblikket i en <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>eller <xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>, som medlem eller -objektet er hoppet over.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlNodeType>

trans-unit.source: For other <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A> values, no action is taken other than calling <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> from the current position.
trans-unit.target: For andre <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>verdier, ingen handling ble utført enn kaller <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A>fra gjeldende posisjon.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.Read%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.NodeType%2A>

trans-unit.source: Subtree readers can call Skip, with behavior restrictions.
trans-unit.target: Undertreet lesere kan ringe Skip, med virkemåte begrensninger.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see the "Subtree Readers" section in <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, or see <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon, kan du se "Undertre lesere"-delen i <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, eller se <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: The node tree behavior of Skip is based on the XML equivalent <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Skip%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Noden tre virkemåten til Skip er basert på XML tilsvarende <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Skip%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Skip%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Based on the <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Skip%2A?displayProperty=fullName> behavior equivalence, Skip skips the node and its subtree, not just the single entry node.
trans-unit.target: Basert på den <xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Skip%2A?displayProperty=fullName>Virkemåte likhet, Skip hopper over noden og tilhørende undertre, ikke bare én oppføring noden.</xref:System.Xml.XmlReader.Skip%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: Releases all resources used by the current instance of the <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Frigir alle ressursene som brukes av den gjeldende forekomsten av den <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlReader"> </xref> klasse.

trans-unit.source: When implemented in a derived class, gets the <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlType"></xref> of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når implementert i en avledet klasse, henter den <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlType"> </xref> for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: Subtree readers can call Type, with behavior restrictions.
trans-unit.target: Undertreet lesere kan ringe typen med virkemåte begrensninger.

trans-unit.source: For more information, see the "Subtree Readers" section in <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, or see <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.
trans-unit.target: For mer informasjon, kan du se "Undertre lesere"-delen i <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>, eller se <xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A>.</xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader.ReadSubtree%2A> </xref:System.Xaml.XamlReader>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlType"></xref> of the current node; or <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>, if the current reader position is not on an object.
trans-unit.target: Den <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlType"> </xref> for den gjeldende noden; eller <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>, hvis posisjonen i leseren ikke er et objekt.

trans-unit.source: When implemented in a derived class, gets the value of the current node.
trans-unit.target: Når implementert i en avledet klasse, henter verdien for den gjeldende noden.

trans-unit.source: The value of the current node; or <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""></xref>, if the current reader position is not on a <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlNodeType"></xref> node type.
trans-unit.target: Verdien for den gjeldende noden. eller <xref uid="langword_csharp_null" name="null" href=""> </xref>, hvis posisjonen i leseren er på en <xref href="System.Xaml.XamlNodeType"> </xref> nodetype.
